Anh - Anh
aporia
[ə'pɔ:rɪə, ə'pɒrɪə]
■ noun
1》 an irresolvable internal contradiction or logical disjunction in a text, argument, or theory.
2》 Rhetoric the expression of doubt.
Derivatives
aporeticadjective
Origin
C16: via late L. from Gk, from aporos 'impassable'.
